KATSINA – The Alumni Association of National Institute AANI Katsina State Chapter has organized a dinners in honour of the participants of course 44 who were on study tour to the state. The study tour is part of the requirements for the fulfillment of the award of the mni at the National Institute for Policy and strategic Studies Kuru Jos. The area of Study for the course 44 participants, is strengthening Local Government Administration in Nigeria. -Advertisement- Speaking at the dinner, the Kanwan Katsina district Head of Ketare, Alhaji Usman Bello Kankara mni suggested that, for the Local Government administration to be strengthen, productivity must be improved and autonomy granted them. The former Customs boss who is also a member of the Alumni course 35, 2013 said there is need to set up mechanisms of checks and balances in the local government service to ensure prudent management of resources. He further stated that, there is need for the local governments in the country to improve their internally generated revenue to reduce the over dependence on federal allocation. Kankara who stressed the importance of training and retraining of local government staff, advocated for the improvement of reward and punishment as a yard stick to measure performance. Others who spoke during the dinner include the Katsina State chairman of the Alumni Association of National Institute, NIPSS, Alhaji Lawal Aliyu Daura mni and retired Assistant Inspector General of Police Danlami Yar’adua among others.